model.name: Modified - Smallbone2013 - Glycolysis in S.cerevisiae - Iteration 18

body.div: Modified - Smallbone2013 - Glycolysis in S.cerevisiae - Iteration 18

div.p: This model is a modification of the model described in the article:

div.a: A model of yeast glycolysis based on a consistent kinetic characterization of all its enzymes

div.div: Kieran Smallbone, Hanan L. Messiha, Kathleen M. Carroll, Catherine L. Winder, Naglis Malys, Warwick B. Dunn, Ettore Murabito, Neil Swainston, Joseph O. Dada, Farid Khan, Pınar Pir, Evangelos Simeonidis, Irena Spasić, Jill Wishart, Dieter Weichart, Neil W. Hayes, Daniel Jameson, David S. Broomhead, Stephen G. Oliver, Simon J. Gaskell, John E.G. McCarthy, Norman W. Paton, Hans V. Westerhoff, Douglas B. Kell, Pedro Mendes

ul.li: In global quantities energy_charge, fit_conc, and glycerate phosphates are changed from being assignments to fixed at the initial values.
The species AMP, NADH, and UDP-glucose were defined with a max(Values, 0) function ensuring them to be positive. This is changed to not include the max function.

In the original model in the reaction for phosphofructokinase, a minimum function was defined to find the minimum of the two subunits alpha and beta of PFK. This was changed to be PFK2 as this is the lowest.

div.p: The original model is hosted on BioModels Database and identified by: MODEL1303260018 .
To cite BioModels Database, please use: BioModels Database: An enhanced, curated and annotated resource for published quantitative kinetic models .
